    <h2 id="why-womens-vitamins">What Women Actually Need From a Multivitamin</h2>

    <p>Women's nutritional requirements are shaped by unique physiological realities: menstruation depletes iron monthly, pregnancy and breastfeeding dramatically increase folate, iron, and calcium demands, hormonal fluctuations affect nutrient metabolism throughout life, and postmenopausal bone density loss requires calcium and vitamin D optimization. A generic multivitamin fails to adequately address any of these female-specific needs. A properly formulated women's multivitamin is not a marketing gimmick — it is a clinical necessity based on well-documented sex-based differences in nutrient requirements.</p>

