    </div>

    <p>The most important differentiator between women's multivitamins is the form of each nutrient. Methylfolate (active folate) versus folic acid (synthetic, requires conversion that 30-40% of women cannot efficiently perform due to MTHFR variants). Chelated iron (gentle on the stomach) versus ferrous sulfate (causes constipation and nausea). Vitamin D3 (human bioidentical form) versus D2 (plant-derived, less effective). These form differences determine whether a supplement delivers real clinical benefit or merely checks a marketing box.</p>

