    <!-- FAQ SECTION -->
    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions About Gummies for Women</h2>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>What vitamins do women need most?</summary>
      <p>Iron (18mg for premenopausal women), folate (400-800mcg for all women of childbearing age), calcium + vitamin D (bone density — 4x osteoporosis risk vs men), omega-3 DHA (brain and heart health), and biotin (hair, skin, nails).</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Is a women's multivitamin different from a general one?</summary>
      <p>Yes. Women's formulas have higher iron (18mg vs 8mg), higher folate (neural tube prevention), more calcium and D (osteoporosis), biotin for beauty, and sometimes hormonal support herbs like chasteberry. General multivitamins use middle-ground doses that miss female-specific needs.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Should women take iron in a gummy vitamin?</summary>
      <p>Premenopausal women need 18mg iron daily. Most gummy vitamins omit iron due to taste and formulation challenges. Olly and MegaFood include iron. Otherwise, take a separate iron gummy. Postmenopausal women need only 8mg daily.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>When should women start taking folate?</summary>
      <p>The CDC recommends ALL women ages 15-45 consume 400mcg daily, regardless of pregnancy plans. 50% of pregnancies are unplanned, and neural tube defects occur in the first 28 days. Methylfolate works for everyone, including MTHFR variant carriers.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>What is the best gummy vitamin for women over 50?</summary>
      <p>Women 50+ need more calcium and vitamin D (osteoporosis), higher B12 (absorption declines with age), less iron (post-menopause), and cognitive nutrients (omega-3, B vitamins). Choose a 50+ formula or adjust your supplement stack accordingly.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Can gummy vitamins help with hair, skin, and nails?</summary>
      <p>Biotin supports keratin production for hair and nails. Vitamin C enables collagen synthesis for skin. Vitamin E provides antioxidant skin protection. Many women's formulas include 2,500-5,000mcg biotin. For targeted beauty support, add a dedicated biotin or collagen gummy.</p>
    </details>

